    &lt;CommentText&gt;As the matron who oversees the placing of patients in surgery I am very sorry to hear about your experience. As you suggest there are reasons why we are currently having to use SALs for our inpatients and it is never an option taken lightly. The main reason is to enable us to continue operating whilst the Jubilee wards undergo some urgent pipeworks which entails closing 24 beds at a time.  
Thank you for so clearly identifying the issues which you have encountered. I will see where we can improve the situation for the patients who are taken there for periods of care.  
